In this proclamation, President Barack Obama declares November 15, 2014, as America Recycles Day. He emphasizes the importance of leaving a cleaner and more sustainable world for future generations. The President highlights the benefits of recycling, such as reducing energy consumption, greenhouse gas emissions, and conserving natural resources. He also mentions the creation of green jobs and support for the manufacturing sector. The proclamation encourages individuals, businesses, and communities to increase their recycling efforts. The Federal Government aims to lead by example in reducing environmental impact, and American businesses are encouraged to reflect their commitment to recycling in their bottom line. The proclamation calls upon Americans to observe America Recycles Day with appropriate programs and activities and to continue reducing, reusing, and recycling throughout the year.